<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="343" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,295,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[353,413,475,501]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">India</collectingCountry>
, the species was found three times, but the morphometric data on the Indian specimens are very scanty (mostly limited to the total body length). More detailed data from living animals would be appreciated to confirm species identification on morphological ground.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,295,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Moreover, comparison on molecular genetics data would confirm or disprove the cosmopolitan distribution of the species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
